On Thu, 26 Jul 2001, David Honig wrote:

> Bear has a point; no matter how you spread or hop, you're an emitter.
> Shoot anything that radiates from 50 Mhz-IR.

Ultrabroadband is currently hard to triangulate, unless you're part of the
network, where TOF mutual triangulation is part of service.

You could triangulate ultrabroadband with an antenna array, but in real
life the reflexion and multipath will make it difficult.

